  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposal would fail to respect the principles laid out in section 2.4.2 of the statutory Urban Design Guide (2006) by disrupting the largely unaltered roofline of the terrace to the detriment of the appearance of the surrounding Conservation Area.  In addition, due to long views of the property from St Marys Path and the churchyard the proposed roof extension would contravene Section 18.13 and 18.15 of the Upper Street (North) Conservation Area Design Guidelines which stipulates that roof extensions which are visible from public views will not be permitted.  The proposal would also fail to comply with policy CS9 of the Core Strategy (2011); policies D3, D4, D11 and D25 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002)."
